<h2>What Does This Mean?</h2>
<p>These are averages of people in the same income range and region as you.
    Your situation is unique so you may need to spend more in some categories 
    than the average person. Some of these categories may not even apply to you
    or you may classify your spending differently.
    </P>
<p>
    You should also keep in mind that the average person in lower income ranges does not have much money in savings. 
    A healthy savings account gives you more opportunities and protects you from risk. The most importnt thing is that you spend less
    money than you make and try to build up you savings.
</p>